        <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Born in Columbus, Ohio in 1874. When Heffner was 10 years old he and his family moved
                to California in 1884. As young man he worked as a bookkeeper at the First National
                Bank in Los Angeles, California. After the bank closed in 1893, Heffner asked one of
                the banks customer's, Walter Vail (owner of the Empire Ranch) if he had any work for
                him. Thus began his career in the cattle business. Heffner served as the manger of
                the Vail and Gates Empire Ranch, Pima County, Ariz. from 1893 to 1905. Heffner was
                one of the founding members of the Arizona Cattle Growers' Asssociation and served
                as it's first secretary.</p>
        </bioghist>
